# URLs lychee must not try to resolve. One regex per line.
#
# 1. Hosts with no dot in them are never internet URLs. Two sources in this repo, both
#    uncheckable from CI by construction:
#      a) Cluster-internal service names in Gateway/HTTPRoute manifests and in the DR
#         runbook — https://budget/, https://dex/, https://backstage/. They resolve only
#         inside the cluster.
#      b) Mis-parses of cosign keyless-identity REGEXES. lychee stops at the backslash, so
#         '^https://token\.actions\.githubusercontent\.com$' is reported as https://token/
#         and '^https://github\.com/...' as https://github/. These are signature-verification
#         patterns, not links — rewriting them to satisfy a link checker would break image
#         verification.
^https?://[^./]+/?$

# 2. Private ingress hostnames. They resolve on the home network only.
^https?://.*\.lan(/|$)
^https?://.*\.svc\.cluster\.local(/|$)
^https?://dex\.dev\.platform\.devantler\.tech(/|$)
